26 552.445 Property damage caused by limestone mining
27 operations; legislative findings and intent.—
28 (1) The Legislature finds that:
29 (a) Limestone mining for aggregate is an essential
30 component of this state's economy, contributing to
31 infrastructure development and construction by providing a cost-
32 effective source of concrete.
33 (b) Limiting limestone mining operations would result in
34 increased costs of construction, adversely affecting this
35 state's economy and its residents.
36 (2) The Legislature also recognizes the concerns of
37 residents in North West Miami-Dade County and South West Broward
38 County, who have reported property damage resulting from ground
39 vibrations caused by nearby limestone mining operations.
40 (3) It is the intent of the Legislature to provide a fair
41 and equitable remedy for property owners who can prove that
42 their property damage was caused by nearby limestone mining
43 operations.
44 Section 2. Section 552.4451, Florida Statutes, is created
45 to read:
46 552.4451 Definitions.—As used in ss. 552.445-552.4454, the
47 term:
48 (1) "Claimant" means a property owner who files a claim
49 for compensation for property damage caused by limestone mining
50 operations.
