51 (2) "Division" means the Division of Administrative
52 Hearings.
53 (3) "Ground vibrations" means seismic activity in the
54 ground caused by the use of explosives, heavy machinery, or
55 other mining operations involved in limestone extraction or
56 processing. Such activity may be mechanically detected by
57 seismographic monitoring or other means within a radius of up to
58 3 miles from the point of origin.
59 (4) "Limestone mining operation" means the extraction and
60 processing of limestone for use in concrete aggregate which
61 results in ground vibrations.
62 (5) "Property damage" means any physical damage to a
63 structure, a foundation, or property caused by ground vibrations
64 or a related impact resulting from limestone mining operations.
65 (6) "Property owner" means an individual or entity holding
66 title to real property in this state.
67 Section 3. Section 552.4452, Florida Statutes, is created
68 to read:
69 552.4452 Claims; statute of limitations.—
70 (1) A property owner whose property is located within a 3
71 mile radius of limestone mining operations who has sustained
72 property damage as a result of such operations has the right to
73 file a claim for compensation.
74 (2) A claim for compensation must include all of the
75 following:
