103 Section 5. Section 552.4454, Florida Statutes, is created
104 to read:
105 552.4454 Appropriation and compensation.—
106 (1) The Legislature shall appropriate each fiscal year
107 from the General Revenue Fund moneys to the Insurance Regulatory
108 Trust Fund to ensure the prompt payment of compensation awarded
109 by an administrative law judge under s. 552.4453.
110 (2)(a) If a claim is upheld by the administrative law
111 judge under s. 553.4453, the state must compensate the claimant
112 for costs to repair structural damage to the claimant's
113 property.
114 (b) Compensation amounts are determined based on the
115 market rates for such repair costs.
